It's unclear what sparked the fire yesterday afternoon, which also left another person in a critical condition. CAPE TOWN - The Western Cape Social Development Department is investigating a fire at an old age home in Langa that killed one person.It's unclear what sparked the fire yesterday afternoon, which also left another person in a critical condition.Residents were quickly evacuated from the premises and no other injuries were reported.Provincial Social Development MEC Albert Fritz says: The Western Cape government wants to extend condolences to the family of the man who died in the fire. The Departed of Social Development will investigate what happened. (Edited by Shimoney Regter)